# Style and Formatting

## Naming Conventions
- Use `snake_case` for variables and function names.
- Use `PascalCase` for class names.

## Code Formatting
- Use 4 spaces per indent level.
- Limit lines to 88 characters (follow Black formatting).

## Git Pre-commit Hook
- Use git pre-commit hooks to automatically run Black and isort before each commit.
- This ensures consistent code formatting across the project.
- Pre-commit hooks should be configured to format code and check for linting issues.